Two possible meanings:

1. Where two subsidiaries of the same parent company accidently sue each other, not realising that they have the same owner.  An analogy is "friendly fire", where a person accidentally shoots someone on his or her own side.

2. Where a person sues another person (friend) purely to settle a point of (unsettled) law.